<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<section xml:lang="en" xml:id="element-em" class="element"
	xmlns="http://purl.oclc.org/NET/dml/1.0/"
	xmlns:cdml="http://purl.oclc.org/NET/cdml/1.0/"
	xmlns:dct="http://purl.org/dc/terms/">

	<title>The <cdml:node role="element">em</cdml:node> element</title>
	<metadata>
		<list>
			<item property="dct:description">An emphasized text.</item>
		</list>
	</metadata>
	<p>The <cdml:node role="element">em</cdml:node> element represents an emphasized text.</p>
	<list>
		<item>
			<title>Flow</title>
			<p href="#inline-flow">Inline</p>
		</item>
		<item>
			<title>Children</title>
			<cdml:code language="xpath">
( $inline | text() )+
			</cdml:code>
		</item>
		<item>
			<title>Attributes</title>
			<cdml:code language="xpath">
( $core.attrs* | $meta.attrs* | @role? )
			</cdml:code>
		</item>
		<item>
			<title>Parents</title>
			<cdml:code language="xpath">
( $block | $inline )
			</cdml:code>
		</item>
	</list>

	<p>The <cdml:node role="attribute">role</cdml:node> attribute <em>may</em> be used to provide strong emphasized text with <cdml:value>strong</cdml:value> value.</p>

	<example>
		<title>Usage of <cdml:node role="element">em</cdml:node> element</title>
		<cdml:code language="xml">
&lt;p&gt;
  &lt;em&gt;Lorem ipsum&lt;/em&gt; dolor sit amet, consectetur adipisicing elit, sed do &lt;em role="strong"&gt;eiusmod tempor incididunt ut labore&lt;/em&gt; et dolore magna aliqua.
&lt;/p&gt;
		</cdml:code>
	</example>

</section>